They were scavengers, sort of like vultures.<br>
<br>
Once the real hunters had killed something they waited and then ate the scraps and left overs.<br>
Usually this was the marrow bone, to hard to crack open without using a tool.<br>
The &quot;hunters&quot; of old times are merely a myth that was long since abandoned, humans were prey, nothing else.<br>
Sadly we tasted rather good and couldnt fly, so as far as scavengers go we were sort of a failure also.<br>
